CHANGES0013 - Split monolithic work.agda into 8 separate files

REORGANIZATION: The 842-line monolithic work.agda was split into
focused modules for faster incremental compilation.

File structure (dependency order):

1. Trichotomy.agda (29 lines)
   - Tri data type (three-way comparison)
   - IsStrictTotalOrder record

2. CechBase.agda (158 lines) [depends on: Trichotomy]
   - Fiber, Tuple, Ax, Gx, ℤ·, Cochain, sumFin
   - _≤S_, IsStrictlyOrdered, IsWeaklyOrdered
   - OrdTuple, SemiOrdTuple, OrdCochain, SemiOrdCochain
   - π (restriction: standard → ordered), πsemi
   - _<F_, triF, decEqS (fiber trichotomy)
   - Fin≡, fsuc-inj (Fin utilities)
   - parityℕ, signℤ (shared across modules)

3. CechPermutations.agda (103 lines) [depends on: CechBase]
   - Perm, idPerm, applyPerm
   - invCountℕ, permToℕFun, sgnPerm
   - HasRepeat, IsAlternating, VanishesOnRepeats
   - AltCochain, SemiAltCochain, altIncl

4. CechFaceMaps.agda (93 lines) [depends on: CechBase]
   - skip, face (face maps)
   - cechDiff (standard Cech differential)
   - face-preserves-strict, ordDiff (ordered differential)
   - skip-skip (simplicial identity)

5. CechSorting.agda (173 lines) [depends on: CechBase, CechPermutations]
   - sort2, insert, mulSign, signFromSwaps, sortTuple
   - mapRepeatSucc, weakToStrictDec
   - cMap-go, cMap (ordered → standard map)

6. CechProperties.agda (151 lines) [depends on: CechBase, CechPermutations, CechSorting]
   - strict→weak, isPropStrictOrd
   - insert-result<, sortTuple-sorted
   - strict-head-lt, strict-no-repeat
   - π∘c≡id (PROVED)

7. CechDSquared.agda (324 lines) [depends on: CechBase, CechFaceMaps]
   - sumFin-ℤ·, sumFin-0, sumFin-add
   - signℤ-ss, sign-cancel, sign-comm
   - +rearrange, removeIdx, sumFin-extract
   - d²-pair-cancel, Fin helpers
   - removeIdx-inj, removeIdx-misses, removeIdx-surj
   - sumFin-invol-cancel, doubleSum-cancel
   - d²≡0 (PROVED)

8. work.agda (29 lines) [imports all modules]
   - Re-exports everything under CechComplex module

Key changes:
- parityℕ and signℤ moved to CechBase (shared across modules)
- Fixed overlay filesystem mount for cubical library
- All proofs preserved: 0 holes, 0 postulates
- Total: 1060 lines across 8 files (vs 842 monolithic)
  Increase is from repeated module headers/imports.

Benefits:
- Changing one file only triggers recompilation of that file + dependents
- CechDSquared and CechProperties are independent — can compile in parallel
- CechPermutations and CechFaceMaps are independent — can compile in parallel
